## 4.5 Baseline Comparison

### 4.5.1 Mechanism Comparison: f64 Laplace vs Discrete Laplace

We compare the Laplace f64 mechanism (v0.6) against the discrete Laplace (v0.7) on the same parameters (n=100, ε=0.5, α=0.1).

| Property | Laplace f64 (v0.6) | Discrete DLap (v0.7) |
|---|---|---|
| δ | 2.9×10⁻¹⁵ (Mironov 2012) | **0** (exact) |
| LSB leakage | Present | Absent |
| Degeneracy (b<<1) | None | None (r=1000) |
| Variance | 2×(Δ/ε)² = 0.00125 | ≈ 2×(Δ/ε)² = 0.00125 |
| ρ (Last.fm) | 0.9996 | **0.9997** |
| MSE (Last.fm) | 0.0013 | **0.0012** |

**Result**: Discrete DLap achieves δ=0 with no utility loss — variance identical to f64 Laplace at this resolution.

### 4.5.2 Privacy Budget Comparison

| Mechanism | ε per agg | δ per agg | ε_total (k=3) | Guarantee |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| No privacy | 0 | 0 | 0 | None |
| Local DP (RAPPOR) | 1.0 | 0 | 3.0 | ε-LDP |
| Laplace f64 (v0.6) | 0.5 | 2.9×10⁻¹⁵ | 1.5 | (ε,δ)-DP |
| **ANCRE DLap (v0.7)** | **0.5** | **0** | **1.5** | **ε-DP** |
| Gaussian (σ=Δ/ε) | 0.5 | ~10⁻³ | 1.5 | (ε,δ)-DP |

### 4.5.3 Utility Comparison on Last.fm

All mechanisms evaluated on identical windows (K=100, Last.fm hetrec2011).

| Mechanism | ε | ρ (Spearman) | MSE |
|---|---|---|---|
| No privacy (baseline) | — | 1.0000 | 0 |
| Mean (no trim) + DLap | 0.5 | 0.9991 | 0.0018 |
| **TMoM (α=0.1) + DLap** | **0.5** | **0.9997** | **0.0012** |
| TMoM (α=0.2) + DLap | 0.5 | 0.9993 | 0.0016 |
| Local DP (ε=0.5) | 0.5 | 0.9823 | 0.0089 |

**Key findings**:
1. TMoM (α=0.1) outperforms mean without trim — robustness to outliers improves utility.
2. ANCRE achieves 99.97% of no-privacy ranking accuracy at ε=0.5.
3. Local DP at the same ε=0.5 drops to ρ=0.9823 — illustrating the Central DP utility advantage.

### 4.5.4 Effect of ε on Utility

| ε | ρ (TMoM+DLap) | MSE |
|---|---|---|
| 0.1 | 0.9923 | 0.0081 |
| 0.3 | 0.9971 | 0.0029 |
| **0.5** | **0.9997** | **0.0012** |
| 1.0 | 0.9999 | 0.0003 |

ANCRE operates at ε=0.5 — strong privacy with excellent utility. At ε=1.0 (add/remove adjacency bound), ρ=0.9999, confirming that the system remains highly useful even with the conservative adjacency model.

### 4.5.5 K-Anonymity Threshold

| K_MIN | ρ | MSE | Note |
|---|---|---|---|
| 50 | 0.9994 | 0.0014 | Higher sensitivity |
| **100** | **0.9997** | **0.0012** | **ANCRE default** |
| 200 | 0.9998 | 0.0011 | Lower sensitivity |
| 500 | 0.9999 | 0.0006 | Near-baseline |

K_MIN=100 is the operational minimum for meaningful k-anonymity. Increasing K reduces MSE at the cost of requiring more participants per window.

